The Elders’ Caucus of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Osun State yesterday said the re-election of Governor Adegboyega Oyetola has been ordained by God. A communiqué by its Chairman, Chief Sola Akinwumi, after a stakeholders’ meeting in Ilobu, Irepodun Local Government Area, said the caucus resolved to throw its weight behind Oyetola.   ‘Ekiti, Osun polls litmus test for 2023…     826 Plateau pilgrims set for Saudi Arabia     MSSN holds Ummahaat conference   It reads: “God backed Oyetola in the first term and we are certain that his reelection has been ordained. Victory is sure for our party. “We appreciate all steps and activities undertaken by the governor towards ensuring quick transformation of our state through his numerous development projects spread across the State. We enjoin the people to continue to give their support towards Oyetola’s re-election on July 16t Let us troop out to vote for Governor Oyetola.”